    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Surveys which gather geophysical data for a location systematically. In archaeology, refers to prospection techniques, such as ground penetrating radar and magnetic survey, used to locate artefacts and map subsurface archaeological features.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
